J.B. Chemicals Surges to Record on Stake Sale Speculation

-- B y   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-04-20T07:05:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/j-b-chemicals-surges-to-record-on-stake-sale-speculation.html
J.B. Chemicals & Pharmaceuticals
Ltd., an Indian maker of drugs to treat  heart disease , surged in
Mumbai trading on speculation that the company may sell part of
its Russian unit for 14 billion rupees ($315 million).  The stock advanced 7.6 percent to 162.1 rupees as of 12:23
p.m., set for its highest level since Bloomberg began tracking
it in 1991.  “We are hearing the company may sell stake in its
subsidiary,” said Nilesh Karani, head of business development
at Magnum Equity Broking Ltd. in Mumbai.  Executive Director Pranabh Mody couldn’t immediately be
reached on his mobile phone or at his office for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hemal Savai in Mumbai at  at
 hsavai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
